23/02/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During a summit of NATO state and government leaders Tuesday (22 February), NATO member states reaffirmed their strong support for a continued presence of the Alliance in Kosovo.
An official statement expressed NATO's determination to contribute to the UN-led political process of building a multiethnic, peaceful and prosperous society there.
During the meeting, US President George W. Bush appealed to the European leaders to put aside past disputes and build a new era of transatlantic unity.
(BBC, VoA, MPA, Tanjug - 22/02/05)
